------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is an Array?
A.An Array is a place holder that holds a fixed number of values of a single type.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between the Array and ArrayList?
A. An Array is a fixed length data structure whereas ArrayList is a variable length Collection class.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is LinkedList?
A. The LinkedList class is a collection which can contain many objects of the same type, just like the ArrayList.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. How is an ArrayList different from Linked List?
A.An Arraylist is good for storing value ,but manipulating variables make the memory slow, whereas Linked list works
same as ArrayList but manipulating variables will not make the memory slow

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between the HashTable and HashMap?
A.HashMap allows one null key and multiple null values whereas Hashtable doesn't allow any null key or value.
HashMap is generally preferred over HashTable if thread synchronization is not needed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What are the major data structures used in the following areas : RDBMS, Network data model and Hierarchical data model?
A.  RDBMS = Array (i.e. Array of structures)
    Network data model = Graph
    Hierarchical data model = Trees
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. How HashMap works in java?
A. Hashmap interface is an object that applies the concept of key /value .

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException in java? When it occurs?
A. ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException it  is a runtime exception in Java that occurs when an array is accessed with an
unidentified index.

